    <h1>KUBUR KASSIM (above)</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200823/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-23"><time>2020-08-23</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | FEATURES</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Kubur Kassim Ceme­tery was es­tab­lished in the 1920s in Siglap Road on land owned by a cargo-boat and steam-launch owner named Ahna Mo­hamed Kassim Ally Mo­hamed. The Siglap and Be­dok ar­eas were known to have a num­ber of an­cient Mus­lim grave­yards called Mo­hammedan ceme­ter­ies.</p>
    <p>To­day, Kubur Kassim is a non­de­script plot with flow­er­ing frangi­pani trees, sur­rounded on all sides by landed res­i­den­tial prop­er­ties and con­do­mini­ums.</p>
    <p>When I vis­ited the site last Satur­day night to take some pho­to­graphs for this fea­ture, my trusty iPhone 11 Pro, which usu­ally takes sharp pictures in low light, sud­denly stopped work­ing.</p>
    <p>After about half an hour of wrestling with the con­trols, I fi­nally man­aged a few shots, be­fore the cam­era froze up again.</p>


